name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:

If you are planning to visit cathedrals, it is recommended to check the opening and closing times on the days you are in the city so you can make the most out of seeing the outside as well as the inside. The interior has really nice architecture and is an impressive Lutheran style design and rich history behind this building.
The cathedral is quite simple to get to and transport is easy to navigate and get around in the city.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: This cathedral is one of the foremost historical landmarks in Helsinki. While the building is architecturally beautiful inside and out, the inside reflects the "less is more" Lutheran simplistic style. There are other beautiful buildings surrounding the Senate square, notably the National Library of Finland which we were only made aware of by our knowledgeable guide, Soili, at the Cathedral. She patiently guided us through the inside and outside of the Cathedral, also taking us up the winding stone staircase to the organ loft where we could view the ornate 1840s-era pipe organ and see where the choir assembles. Our experience was greatly enhanced by Soili's guidance and generous sharing of information and anecdotes about the interior and exterior structures and historic significance.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

Its location is very central so as a tourist you can go to several places within the area as well and maximize your time.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: The White Cathedral in Helsinki, officially known as Helsinki Cathedral, is a stunning masterpiece of neoclassical architecture that stands as one of the city’s most iconic landmarks. Its majestic white façade, adorned with elegant green domes and golden crosses, exudes an air of tranquility and grandeur. Located in the heart of Senate Square, the cathedral offers a breathtaking view of the surrounding cityscape and is a must-visit for anyone exploring Helsinki. The interior, though simple, boasts an exquisite organ and serene atmosphere perfect for reflection. Visitors can climb up to the dome for panoramic views of the city and the Baltic Sea. The cathedral’s timeless beauty and historical significance make it a perfect destination for photography enthusiasts, history buffs, and anyone seeking to experience Helsinki’s rich cultural heritage. Whether visited in the glow of summer or the crispness of winter, the White Cathedral is a symbol of elegance and grace that leaves an indelible impression on all who see it.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Visiting the Helsinki Cathedral is an immersive experience that allows you to appreciate not just its exterior beauty but also the rich history and culture it represents. The cathedral’s construction dates back to the mid-19th century, and its design by architect Carl Ludvig Engel reflects the influence of classical Greek architecture.

As you approach the cathedral, you’re greeted by its impressive staircase and facade, which exude a sense of grandeur and elegance. The intricate details, including the statues, columns, and reliefs, showcase the craftsmanship of the era.

Stepping inside, you’re enveloped in a serene atmosphere enhanced by the cathedral’s high ceilings, ornate decorations, and beautiful stained glass windows. The interior features a stunning altar, majestic organ, and historical artifacts that provide insights into Finland’s religious and cultural heritage.

One of the highlights of visiting the Helsinki Cathedral is ascending to its observation deck. From there, you’re treated to panoramic views of Helsinki and the surrounding area, offering a unique perspective of the city’s layout and landmarks.

Whether you’re interested in architecture, history, or simply appreciating stunning views, the Helsinki Cathedral offers something for everyone. It’s not just a religious site but also a symbol of Finnish identity and a testament to the country’s rich artistic and architectural heritage. A visit to Helsinki wouldn’t be complete without experiencing the grandeur and beauty of this iconic cathedral.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Helsinki Cathedral, a crown jewel of Finnish architecture, stands majestically in Senate Square as one of the city’s most iconic landmarks. Built between 1830 and 1852, this neoclassical masterpiece is a testament to Helsinki’s cultural and historical evolution.

Historical Insights

Origins and Architectural Significance:

Originally designed by Carl Ludvig Engel, a prominent German architect, the cathedral was conceived as part of a larger plan to redesign Helsinki. The structure was completed in 1852 under the direction of Engel’s successor, Ernst Lohrmann, who added notable features like the zinc statues of the Twelve Apostles on the roof.

Symbol of Russian Influence:

Initially named the Church of St. Nicholas, in honor of Tsar Nicholas I of Russia, the cathedral reflects Helsinki’s historical ties with the Russian Empire. It became a Lutheran cathedral following Finland’s independence in 1917 and was renamed Helsinki Cathedral.

Cultural and Social Role:

Throughout its history, the cathedral has been more than just a place of worship. It has served as a symbol of Finnish identity and resilience, particularly during times of political turmoil. The cathedral also hosts various cultural and social events, emphasizing its role in the community beyond religious services.

Curiosities and Lesser-Known Facts:

•	Architectural Innovations: Lohrmann introduced four small domes to surround the main dome, enhancing the building’s grandeur and setting a precedent in neoclassical architecture.
•	Buried Time Capsule: During its construction, a time capsule containing coins and other artifacts from the era was buried in the cathedral’s cornerstone.
•	Statues of the Apostles: The 12 statues of the apostles on the roof are unique in Northern Europe and were considered innovative for their time.
•	Historical Preservation: Despite Helsinki’s various urban developments, the cathedral has retained its original appearance, a rarity among European churches of similar age.

Visitor Experience

Accessibility:

Located in the heart of Helsinki, the cathedral is easily accessible via public transport. Its central location makes it a convenient stop in any city tour.

Exterior Exploration:

Even if entry is not possible, the grandeur of the cathedral can be appreciated from outside. The imposing steps leading up to the entrance and the panoramic views from the square offer a glimpse into its architectural brilliance.

Senate Square:

Adjacent to the cathedral, Senate Square hosts various events and provides a historical backdrop that enriches the overall experience of visiting the area. It’s a great place for photography, offering stunning views of the cathedral.

Tips for Incorporating into a City Itinerary:

1.	Morning Visit: Start your day with a visit to the cathedral. Its early morning light provides excellent photo opportunities.
2.	Walking Tour: Combine your visit with a walking tour of Senate Square and the nearby University of Helsinki and Government Palace.
3.	Café Stop: After exploring, relax at one of the local cafés around the square, which offer a perfect vantage point to enjoy the cathedral’s beauty.
4.	Cultural Sites: Include nearby cultural attractions such as the Ateneum Art Museum or the National Library of Finland in your itinerary.

Conclusion:

Despite not being able to enter on the day of your visit, Helsinki Cathedral’s historical and architectural significance, coupled with its prime location, makes it a must-see in Helsinki. Its enduring legacy as a symbol of Finnish culture and its striking neoclassical design earn it a well-deserved rating of 4/5.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Helsinki Cathedral, overlooking Senate Square, is a striking symbol of Finnish architecture and national identity. The square itself serves as a vibrant gathering place, surrounded by historic buildings and cultural landmarks, offering a glimpse into Helsinki's rich heritage.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Minimalistic Lutheran Church conceptualised by Carl Ludwig. The simplistic design, with white as the primary colour, is majestic in its own right and stands in contrast to the Orthodox Cathedral nearby. White statues of Martin Luther and other leaders of the reformation blend in with the Church walls and, in a certain way, try to keep the focus on the worship.
The location of the Church on the Senate Square with the statue of Alexander II facing it is symbolic of the 19th century link between religion and the state.
There is a voluntary €5 entry fee expected to be paid by visitors.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Both the interior and exterior of the church are truly awesome. Situated atop a hill in the city centre, the location lends a remarkable look to the church.

The church forms a significant part of Helsinki's Empire-era centre and serves as a prominent landmark for those arriving by sea. It symbolizes the entire city of Helsinki. Previously known as St. Nicholas Church and Great Cathedral, this magnificent church, which now serves as the main church of the Helsinki Diocese, was finished in 1852. Adorning the roof of the church, sculptures of the twelve apostles stand as guardians of the city.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: This is not only a monument of Helsinki but a very famous landmark and one of the most important tourist attractions in the country. There's an easy flight of stairs to get to the cathedral and once up there, you can sit on the stairs and spend some time to appreciate the beauty of the city and the Senate square.  Inside the cathedral is a solemn place to reflect and pray. When I visited the church, there was a church activity, although I didn't actively participate, I was able to respectfully observe the Lutheran faith. I also got the chance to listen to the beautiful sound of the church organ when it was playing during the communion. Entrace to the church is free but there is a donation box for the generous visitors. Getting here from the Central Station takes about a leisurely 10-minute walk.

The cathedral is also situated in a lovely square surrounded by other historic buildings, making it a perfect spot for taking in the sights of Helsinki. Whether you are a history buff, an architecture enthusiast, or simply looking for a beautiful place to visit, Helsinki Cathedral is definitely worth a stop on your itinerary.

That was very impressive to me since the Tetragrammaton has been taken out of most bible translations. But yet this very old Cathedral features it prominently above one of the main doors.

While still typical of an European church, they do have a daily engagement session with the public, which is a breath of fresh air. But in the same vein they do also ask for donations for entrance at 5 Euros and charges toilet usage at 2 Euros.

Architecturally wise they're quite impressive, exterior and interior, but nothing really different in terms of how church goes.

If you're here at the Cathedral, be sure to climb the stairs to get a breath taking view of the Senate square below.

When you visiting the Cathedral also pay attention to the status of Alexander II and study the history.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Helsinki Cathedral

￼
Helsinki Cathedral is perhaps the most iconic edifice in Helsinki’s cityscape. The chalk-white, blue-domed Helsinki Cathedral dominates the Senate Square from its position above the stairs leading to it from the square.
The cathedral was also designed by Carl Ludwig Engel but was only finished in 1852, 12 years after his demise.
Its exterior is graced by statues of 16th-century Protestant reformers like Martin Luther and Philipp Melanchthon, and Mikael Agricola, who translated the Bible into Finnish. Its interior is quite spartan as is customary with most Lutheran churches.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Helsinki Cathedral is a church build on a rock. And it's location served the purpose of a religious faith which is, among many other things, to "look up" from your life on Earth to the spiritual plane.

The Cathedral is located in Senatorii Square. It's spritual focus is a bit marred by the huge "My Helsinki" sign at the top of the very steep stone staircase. Adding a touch of "tourism" to a church visit is jarring

Getting up to the balcony outside the church is more easily done by walking up the side street to the church's left when looking at the church head on.

Wearing flat shoes will help you considerably walking the cobblestones of the square and climbing up the stairs to the cathedral

It is useful to describe the church's architecture by comparing it with the Ouspensky Orthodox Church in Helsinki. Where Ouspensky is reddish brown brick, Helsinki Cathedral is white. The interior walls are white in the Lutheran Cathedral, with just a few statues, always included is Martin Luther. The only concession to an adorned theology are two angels in the front of the church. Ouspensky if full of Religious icons, and gilded woodwork. Ouspensky had a much more attractive cupola to look up and see heaven.

Helsinki Cathedral like Ouspensky rises up and tower o er their neighborhoods and that affords you very interesting peek-a-boo views from many areas of the city. I have included one here.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Beautiful and iconic cathedral located in the centre of Helsinki, capital of Finland is a must visit, located at the Senate Square. The church was originally built from 1830–1852 as a tribute to the Grand Duke of Finland, Tsar Nicholas I of Russia. It is a major landmark of the city, and possibly the most famous structure in Finland as a whole when viewed globally. It's equally beautiful during the day and night time.The day we went it was not too crowded, we could sit  peacefully to offer prayers. It was quite rejuvenating.j

name: Helsinki Cathedral

Mint and white, It's a beautiful color that comes to mind when you think of Finland. So I went in with anticipation, but I think the inside was a little bit impractical. I think it would have been grand enough to use a large dome in the middle as a room.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Built between 1830-1852, towering over Market Square. It is a major landmark with a steep set of stairs, the church is modelled after Saint Isaac’s Cathedral in St. Petersburg. There are statues of the Apostles made of zinc on the roof, and they are the biggest unique set of zinc sculptures in the world.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
ヘルシンキ大聖堂は19世紀前半にフィンランドを支配していたロシア皇帝・フィンランド大公のニコライ一世を顕彰して建てられた教会だという。その後20世紀前半にロシア革命が起こりフィンランドが独立すると本協会も正教会からプロテスタントのルーテル派に変わったそうだ。

欧州のキリスト教国において国を代表する教会はえてして華美で荘厳に作られている印象だが、この聖堂はヘルシンキを、そしてフィンランドを代表する教会でありながら見た目も内装も比較的簡素で、素朴な印象さえ受ける。それが長らく周辺諸国の支配を受けてきた歴史ゆえのものか、フィンランドの国風によるものかは分からないが、個人的には素朴な大聖堂というのも良いと思う。

name: Helsinki Cathedral

Dentro è molto spoglia. L’organo è impressionante.

Wenn man durch die Stadt schlendert, kann diese Kirche nicht verpfehlen. Auch ein gute Standpunkt um sich zu treffen. Wer eine Reise nach Helsinki plant, dem kann ich diesen Ort sehr empfehlen.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: La Cattedrale di Helsinki è una chiesa evangelica luterana, considerata un simbolo e punto di riferimento importante. Attualmente ci sono dei lavori in corso, si entra dalla porta della scalinata e non viene richiesto un pagamento. Esternamente molto elegante e maestosa. Progettata dall'architetto tedesco Engel e l'urbanista Ehreström, una targhetta commemorativa si trova nei pressi della cattedrale. Il suo interno è semplice ed è costruita a forma di croce greca. Nessuno è mai stato sepolto nel terreno della chiesa, però una parte di Piazza del Senato era adibita a cimitero. Quando fu spianata per la costruzione della cattedrale i defunti non furono spostati. Il campanile è separato in quanto sostituite le campane erano troppo grandi e non era più sufficiente lo spazio nel vecchio campanile. Luogo di silenzio all'interno. Una visita assolutamente.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
ヘルシンキ大聖堂はヘルシンキ市街のほぼ中央に位置しています。その一画は少し小高くなっており、大聖堂がどの方角に見えるかで自分の位置を知る事が出来ます。ケルンやミラノの大聖堂と違い緑の丸いドームと純白の壁に威厳よりも寧ろ優しさを感じます。Sofiankatu 通やヘルシンキ港から眺める大聖堂も素敵です。

残念ながら、時間的に遅くなって入場出来なかったのは大変残念でした。

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Eher schlicht von innen, aber die Orgel hört sich toll an. Die Crypta ist zugänglich und wunderbar kühl im Moment und schön hergerichtet mit einem Cafe 👍😎

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Der Dom mit seinen hohen weißen Säulen, die in einer grünen Kuppel enden, ist schon von weitem zu sehen. Die äußere Opulenz wird durch das sehr bescheidene, fast leere Innere des Gebäudes in Kontrast gesetzt. Der Eintritt ist frei. Um in die Kathedrale zu gelangen, muss man ein paar Stufen hinaufsteigen. Vor der Treppe erstreckt sich der Senatsplatz, in dessen Mitte sich die Statue von Zar Alexander II. befindet.
Auf diesem Platz finden verschiedene Veranstaltungen statt. Während unserer Reise wurde die Zeremonie des MICHELIN Guide Nordic Countries 2024 live auf den Bildschirm übertragen.

Merdivenleri tırmandığınızda Helsinki’yi yukarıdan görme olanağı bulursunuz. Hop on-hop off denilen tur otobüslerinin güzergahı üzerindedir. Meydanda güzel kafeler de yer alır. Helsinki’yi ziyaret edenler için güzel bir ziyaret noktası olacaktır.

review_text:
A igreja é linda por fora e por dentro.
Mas acho um pecado igrejas do mundo todo cobrarem um valor fixo de ingresso.
Parece que se tornou um comércio e acho vergonho fazer isso com "a casa de deus".
Igreja deveria ser um local dedicado a escutar as pessoas, orar com elas e ajudá-las a encontrar o caminho certo.
Os próprios membros da igreja não perguntam nem como você está.
Arquitetura nota 10
Como missão de igreja, não vi nenhum trabalho em tempo integral.
Logo vale ser visitado como ponto turístico e não como local religioso.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Ao pouco de Helsinki converterse na capital de Finlandia, en 1812, Alexandro I de Rusia decretou que unha parte dos impostos do sal debían destinarse á construción de dúas igrexas, unha luterana e outra ortodoxa. Esta catedral luterana levantada despois como homenaxe a Nicolás I, zar de Rusia e gran duque de Finlandia, foi construída entre os anos 1830 e 1852. Erixiuse sobre unha pequena igrexa de 1727 que estaba adicada a Ulrica Leonor, raíña de Suecia. O seu arquitecto foi o alemán Carl Ludvig Engel e máis adiante o finlandés Ernst Lohrmann encargouse de engadir as catro cúpulas máis pequenas, os dous campanarios e as estatuas dos Doce Apóstolos, situadas nas esquinas do tellado, elaboradas en zinc. Ata o ano 1917 da independencia do país, esta edificación relixiosa era coñecida como Igrexa de San Nicolás. Xunto coa contigua praza do Senado e os edificios adxacentes, constitúen a estampa máis simbólica da cidade.

Βρίσκεται σε μια μεγάλη πλατεία με σκαλοπάτια και σίγουρα τις γιορτές με τους στολισμούς θα είναι ακόμα πιο εντυπωσιακός. Δεν νομίζω να υπάρχει επισκέπτης της πόλης που να μην έχει κάνει ένα πέρασμα από τον ναό.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: È la seconda volta che ho l’opportunità di visitare questa cattedrale ed ogni volta mi lascia senza parole come la prima. name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
La Cattedrale di Helsinki, situata nella piazza del Senato, è senza dubbio uno dei simboli più iconici della capitale finlandese. Questo imponente edificio bianco, con la sua caratteristica cupola verde, domina il panorama della città e attira ogni anno migliaia di visitatori.

Costruita nel XIX secolo in stile neoclassico, la cattedrale è un esempio straordinario di architettura, sia per la sua semplicità elegante che per la sua maestosità. All'interno, l'atmosfera è sobria e serena, con linee pulite e un design minimalista che riflette perfettamente l'estetica luterana. Le ampie vetrate permettono alla luce naturale di illuminare lo spazio, creando un ambiente di pace e contemplazione.

La cattedrale non è solo un luogo di culto, ma anche un importante punto di riferimento storico e culturale per la città. Spesso ospita concerti ed eventi speciali, arricchendo l'esperienza di chi la visita. Salire le ampie scalinate che conducono all'ingresso principale è quasi un rituale per chiunque visiti Helsinki, e la vista dalla sommità offre una prospettiva mozzafiato sulla piazza del Senato e sulla città circostante.

In definitiva, la Cattedrale di Helsinki è una tappa obbligata per chi visita la città, non solo per la sua bellezza architettonica, ma anche per la sua importanza storica e culturale. Un luogo che lascia un'impressione duratura e che invita alla riflessione e alla meraviglia.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
赫爾辛基】位於芬蘭灣，地處北歐最深處的港口，十六世紀由瑞典國王古斯塔夫所建，十八世紀時已成為當時重要的海上交通要衝。為世上緯度第二高的首都，僅次於冰島首都雷克雅維克。此地最特別的是洋溢俄國風味的古建築與市區景觀。享有「波羅的海少女」的美稱。
【烏斯別斯基東正教大教堂】北歐最大的東正教教堂，完成於
1868 年。洋蔥頭式的綠色屋頂相當醒目，上面頂著面向東方的十字架，總共有13 座尖塔，代表耶穌及十二門徒。教堂內部金碧輝煌，呈現拜占庭藝術風格，包括以蛋彩畫繪製的耶穌及十二門徒壁畫。
【磐石教堂】完成於1969年，磐石教堂顧名思義是利用岩石高地建造而成，為了不損及自然景觀，將岩石部分往下挖掘，教堂就巧妙地設計在其中，其內部的牆上處處有岩石開鑿後的凹凸痕跡，教堂頂部採圓型設計，整座教堂如同著陸地球的飛碟，造型相當獨特。
【西貝流士紀念公園】為紀念芬蘭愛國作曲家西恩.西貝流士（Jean Sibelius•1865-1957）而建。西貝流士被視為民族主義和浪漫主義音樂晚期重要代表。重要作品《芬蘭頌》運用了大量激昂憤概、氣勢磅礡的音樂，喚起當時芬蘭人民的愛國之心。園中最重要的，便是西貝流士紀念碑，以數百條鋼管組合而成，造型前衛。

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: 広い階段の上にある白い綺麗な教会です。ヘルシンキのシンボル的な存在で人気があります。階段の段数は思った以上にありました。

Sehr schön...

L'accesso alla Chiesa é a pagamento e, pertanto, anche sulla base delle recensioni che non la ritenevano particolarmente attraente, l'abbiamo visitata solo esternamente. Per chi ama gli edifici religiosi.

Mais ne payez pas pour voir l'intérieur ! 8€ pour pas grand chose... C'est pas la plus belle église à l'intérieur.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Es sieht einfach atemberaubend aus. Es sticht einfach hervor. Allerdings waren wir wegen einer Veranstaltung nicht drin.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

Dom zu Helsinki auch das "weiß Herz" genannt.
Gehört zu den Hauptattraktion in der Stadt.
Ein beeindruckender Bau von außen.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: L'edificio in se non è molto grande ma la sua collocazione rialzata lo fa sembrare veramente imponente. La piazza antistante, Piazza del Senato, è molto larga e ne offre un'ottima visuale. Le altre recensioni dicono che la chiesa è brutta perché vuota.. Essendo una chiesa luterana è volutamente spoglia e semplice. All'interno sono presenti due sculture di Lutero e Agricola.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Déçus par le prix afin de bénéficier de l’entrée à la cathédrale qui s’élève tout de même à 8€/personne. La beauté de ce lieu réside selon moi à l’extérieur de la cathédrale surplombant ses grands escaliers et sa place. Surtout que l’on peut accéder gratuitement à la crypte depuis l’arrière de la cathédrale (s’y trouve un bar accessible au public), ce que j’ai préféré de la visite.
Bien sûr, l’intérieur de celle-ci reste un lieu de culte pour qui souhaite se recueillir.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Très belle cathédrale. Je suis une passionnée d’histoire et je n’avais jamais eu l’occasion de rentrer dans une église orthodoxe, et je ne suis pas déçue. L’orgue est particulièrement beau . Je vous recommande de visiter ce lieu.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Der 1852 fertiggestellte Dom von Helsinki thront eindrucksvoll über dem Senatsplatz. Das Interieur ist klassisch evangelisch eher schlicht gehalten.

Kostenloser Eintritt, allerdings wird um eine freiwillige Spende in Höhe von 5 Euro gebeten.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

普通、ヨーロッパの教会は金ぴかでゴテゴテした感じですけど、ここは白い空間って感じです。
ドラゴンボールの時間の部屋を思い出した。(^○^)

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
中も外も白くて美しくヘルシンキ大聖堂

ドイツ人建築家のカール　ルートヴィッヒが設計。

1852年に完成。

当時はニコライ教会と呼ばれていたが、1959年に大聖堂として名前が変わった。

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Najbardziej charakterystyczny budynek Finlandii wznosi się na Placu Senackim. Tutaj kończyły się Helsinki, kiedy stały się stolicą Finlandii. Neoklasycystyczny budynek widoczny jest z oddali. Wnętrze typowe dla kościoła protestanckiego, wystrój bardzo skromny. Warto zwrócić uwagę na posągi pierwszych reformatorów.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
ヘルシンキを訪問したら誰もが一度は訪れる名所中の名所。今回は早朝6時にヘルシンキに到着したので、この場所にはまだ誰もいなくてクールな写真を撮ることが出来ました。いつ来ても迫力あり、感動します。夜のさりげないライトアップも素敵ですね。
This is one of the attractions that everyone should visit once when visiting Helsinki. This time I arrived in Helsinki at 6am, so the place was empty and I was able to take some cool pictures. No matter when you come, it is powerful and moving. The casual lighting at night is also wonderful.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: ตั้งอยู่ในจตุรัสใจกลางเมือง สวยงาม อลังการครับ

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
中心駅や港からほど近く、街の中心にある美しい教会です。目の前には大階段があり、その前に広場が広がっています。建物自体はそこまで大きくなく、内部も割とコンパクトですがクリーンで気持ちの良い印象の空間でした。

23年9月に訪問した際には、自主入場料として５ユーロの支払いを求められました。中に入ってすぐの決済端末を使用し、クレジットカードで簡単に支払えます。

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Jak na Helsinki ciekawy kościół i zabytek. W srodku dość surowo. Trafiliśmy na koncert.

近くにお土産屋さんやカフェもあるので楽しいです。
冬は雪が積もるので、階段が大変。
駅からはトラムでも行けます。

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Ein Besuch gehört zur Reise nach Helsinki einfach dazu. Drinnen war ich nicht.

name: Helsinki Cathedral

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
Великолепное грандиозное здание, доминвнта и точка отчета для туристов в городе..
После итальянского и русского избыточного  декора церквей, лютеранская церковь выглядит строго и даже нравоучительно.
Оставляет необыкновенное впечатление от посещения.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Das Innere war leider nur ok. Für den Preis habe ich mich auf mehr gefreut und wurde leider enttäuscht, könnte aber auch meine zu hohen Erwartungen sein, die ich a den Dom hatte, nachdem ich den von außen gesehen habe. Denn dieser ist sehr schön und gut instand gehalten welches wahrscheinlich auf neuliche Renovierungsarbeiten zurückzuführen ist, welche leider in der Zeit meines Aufenthaltes noch nicht fertig waren. Deswegen musste ich mich, wie auf dem Bild zu sehen mit einem dickeren Turm abgeben. Und ja ich schreibe das alles nur um auf die 200 Zeichen zu kommen.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Mooie kerk waar helaas weinig muurschilderingen te vinden zijn. Maar wel een geweldig mooi orgel.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Helsingin yksi hienoimmista nähtävyyksistä .Jokainen kävijä voi sytyttää kynttilän

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text: Ein Muss für jeden Helsinki-Besucher. Der Eintritt ist frei.

name: Helsinki Cathedral
review_text:
芬蘭🇫🇮景點-赫爾辛基大教堂

這是當初19世紀初
送給沙皇尼古拉一世所建的大教堂
一直到1917年芬蘭獨立後
才改名為赫爾辛基大教堂

review_text: Es el edificio símbolo de Helsinki. Situada en un lugar alto, se divisa desde gran parte de la ciudad. Tiene la característica que los cuatro brazos de su cruz griega, rematan en una columnata, lo que hace que no tenga a simple vista una fachada que se destaque. Para visitarla, a veces hay que esperar a que termine un oficio religioso.

赫爾辛基大主教座堂是芬蘭最重要的宗教場所之一，也是芬蘭最著名的地標之一，位於市中心的國會廣場上，是一個充滿歷史和文化意義的場所。

大主教座堂建於19世紀初，是一座新古典主義風格的教堂。它的外觀非常宏偉，擁有白色的希臘式柱子和壯觀的圓頂，可以在城市的不同地方看到它的美麗輪廓。

Helsinki Cathedral is one of the most important religious places in Finland and one of the most famous landmarks in Finland. Located on the Congress Square in the city center, it is a place full of historical and cultural significance.

The Cathedral was built in the early 19th century and is a neoclassical church. Its façade is very grand, with its white Greek columns and imposing dome, its beautiful silhouette can be seen in different parts of the city.

赫爾辛基主教座堂（芬蘭語：Helsingin tuomiokirkko；瑞典語：Helsingfors domkyrka）是芬蘭福音信義會赫爾辛基教區（英語：Diocese of Helsinki）的主教座堂，位於芬蘭首都赫爾辛基市中心的參議院廣場上，左右兩邊分別是芬蘭總理府，赫爾辛基大學主樓和國家圖書館，它也是赫爾辛基坐標性建築。這座教堂最初是獻給俄國沙皇尼古拉一世的，直到1917年芬蘭獨立，都稱為「聖尼古拉教堂」。

德國建築設計師卡爾·路德維格·恩格爾在1830年主持修建了赫爾辛基主教座堂。但是在1840年時，恩格爾病死於赫爾辛基。1840年後，赫爾辛基主教座堂剩下的工作由他的學生繼續完成修建。在1853年，赫爾辛基主教座堂舉辦了首次獻堂典禮。

夜間的赫爾辛基主教座堂

赫爾辛基集市廣場，赫爾辛基主教座堂位於圖片中心
赫爾辛基主教座堂有一個綠色的大圓頂，周圍是四個小圓頂，上方有12位聖徒的雕像。由於赫爾辛基主教座堂以白色為主，所以在舊時候，出海的水手看到教堂就代表了離赫爾辛基越來越近。所以，赫爾辛基又被稱為「白都」。在今天，每到重要節日，在大教堂前的參議院廣場都有盛大的集會或者遊行，構成赫爾辛基市中心的一道獨特風景。教堂興建於1830-1852年，新古典主義風格，能容納1300人。構成參議院廣場的高潮，周邊環繞著其他許多建築。教堂平面為對稱的希臘十字形，四面都有柱廊和三角楣飾。主入口位於西側，祭壇位於東側。四個小圓頂模仿了聖彼得堡的聖以撒大教堂。

今天，大教堂是赫爾辛基的主要景點之一。每年有超過350,000人參觀這座教堂，其中一些人參加宗教儀式，但是大部分只是遊客。它同時也是赫爾辛基大學神學院的禮堂。這座教堂及舉行日常的禮拜，也舉行婚禮等特別活動。

在大教堂興建以前，此處有一座較小的教堂烏爾麗卡·埃利諾拉教堂，獻給瑞典女王烏爾麗卡·埃利諾拉。
